whatever it is

00:26:13.500 --> 00:26:17.370
and dropping it on the
floor was determined

00:26:17.370 --> 00:26:21.280
by the positions of the
particles and momentum

00:26:21.280 --> 00:26:24.660
and so on of particles at
the time of the Big Bang.

00:26:24.660 --> 00:26:27.700
I think that's really
rather ridiculous.

00:26:27.700 --> 00:26:32.290
And that's what strict
determinism says.

00:26:32.290 --> 00:26:37.550
And in Newtonian
mechanics that was true.

00:26:37.550 --> 00:26:41.800
[INAUDIBLE] the greatest
expert on Newtonian mechanics

00:26:41.800 --> 00:26:46.650
said in several different
places that if an Intelligence--

00:26:46.650 --> 00:26:51.940
this Intelligence was spelt
with a capital I-- knew

00:26:51.940 --> 00:26:55.325
the positions of all
positions on momentum

00:26:55.325 --> 00:26:59.740
and so on, of all particles in
the world at any time t zero,

00:26:59.740 --> 00:27:02.480
then that Intelligence
could deduce--

00:27:02.480 --> 00:27:05.420
had to be pretty
intelligent, by the way--

00:27:05.420 --> 00:27:08.670
could deduce their positions and
momenta at all related times.

00:27:08.670 --> 00:27:11.680
That's the property of
Newtonian mechanics.

00:27:11.680 --> 00:27:13.560
And therefore in
Newtonian mechanics--

00:27:13.560 --> 00:27:17.380
if we suppose the Big
Bang known at the time

00:27:17.380 --> 00:27:24.130
of Newtonian mechanics--
it would be true

00:27:24.130 --> 00:27:29.610
that that action of mine in
dropping the whatever it is--

00:27:29.610 --> 00:27:32.980
the Android something
or other-- on the floor

00:27:32.980 --> 00:27:36.440
was determined at the
time of the Big Bang.

00:27:36.440 --> 00:27:38.660
I think that's absolutely
ridiculous to suppose that.

00:27:41.380 --> 00:27:44.490
But anyway, so let me tell
you what the free will

00:27:44.490 --> 00:27:47.350
theorem says now.

00:27:47.350 --> 00:27:50.246
I believe-- but it's
irrelevant what I believe,

00:27:50.246 --> 00:27:51.620
so I shouldn't
even have told you

00:27:51.620 --> 00:27:56.300
what I believe-- that
human experiments have

00:27:56.300 --> 00:28:00.030
the property that they
compress-- suppose I have

00:28:00.030 --> 00:28:02.370
a little box on this table.

00:28:02.370 --> 00:28:04.380
It's got a red button
and a green button,

00:28:04.380 --> 00:28:07.240
or button A and button
B. Then I believe

00:28:07.240 --> 00:28:12.370
that I can press either button
A or button B by a free will

00:28:12.370 --> 00:28:15.310
decision that's independent
of the entire past history

00:28:15.310 --> 00:28:18.860
of the universe
before I press them.

00:28:18.860 --> 00:28:22.640
That I call one bit of free
will-- one binary digit.

00:28:22.640 --> 00:28:26.500
I can make a binary choice
independent of the past history

00:28:26.500 --> 00:28:28.040
of the universe.

00:28:28.040 --> 00:28:33.650
If that is true and various
things about quantum mechanics

00:28:33.650 --> 00:28:39.170
and relativity are true-- or
even approximately true-- then

00:28:39.170 --> 00:28:44.310
it follows that a spin one
particle that I'm experimenting

00:28:44.310 --> 00:28:48.070
on can emerge along
either channel [? C ?]

00:28:48.070 --> 00:28:51.750
or channel D in a manner
independent of the past history

00:28:51.750 --> 00:28:53.240
of the universe.

00:28:53.240 --> 00:28:58.150
That's to say if I have
a certain property,

00:28:58.150 --> 00:29:01.940
this spin one particle has
essentially the same property.

00:29:01.940 --> 00:29:04.180
It can make a binary decision.

00:29:04.180 --> 00:29:06.270
Well, it doesn't actually
make a binary decision.

00:29:06.270 --> 00:29:08.480
It doesn't have to think,
what am I going to do?

00:29:08.480 --> 00:29:10.340
and then do it.

00:29:10.340 --> 00:29:11.400
It just does it.

00:29:11.400 --> 00:29:15.835
It does either C or D
in a manner independent

00:29:15.835 --> 00:29:17.350
of the past history
of the universe.

00:29:17.350 --> 00:29:18.990
That's a theorem.

00:29:18.990 --> 00:29:22.170
That's the free will
theorem that I'm saying.

00:29:22.170 --> 00:29:26.120
It depends on some
uncontentious facts

00:29:26.120 --> 00:29:31.820
about physics, which it's
probably not a good idea for me

00:29:31.820 --> 00:29:35.390
to enumerate right now, because,
I mean, as long as you know

00:29:35.390 --> 00:29:38.360
that they're there-- and
physicists in general,

00:29:38.360 --> 00:29:40.692
have no problem with those.

00:29:40.692 --> 00:29:42.816
SIOBHAN ROBERTS: And the
paper can be found online.

00:29:42.816 --> 00:29:44.149
JOHN HORTON CONWAY: It can, yes.

00:29:44.149 --> 00:29:49.710
Actually there's a
strong version of it--

00:29:49.710 --> 00:29:52.640
the most recent version of it
is called the strong free will

00:29:52.640 --> 00:29:53.140
theorem.

00:29:55.720 --> 00:30:00.780
When we numerated-- well,
one particular-- one

00:30:00.780 --> 00:30:03.640
