00:30:11.710 --> 00:30:15.060
It says, roughly, that
information cannot be

00:30:15.060 --> 00:30:18.650
transmitted faster than
a certain finite speed,

00:30:18.650 --> 00:30:22.590
which you know will
be the speed of light.

00:30:22.590 --> 00:30:28.940
However, that gave rise
to a lot of discussion

00:30:28.940 --> 00:30:31.820
among a certain
group of physicists.

00:30:31.820 --> 00:30:34.371
What does it mean, information?

00:30:34.371 --> 00:30:34.870
Et cetera.

00:30:37.560 --> 00:30:40.350
We thought that that would be
the least troublesome thing,

00:30:40.350 --> 00:30:42.730
but apparently not.

00:30:42.730 --> 00:30:49.680
However, most physicists-- it's
slightly fringe physicists who

00:30:49.680 --> 00:30:53.205
find it problematic.

00:30:53.205 --> 00:30:55.580
SIOBHAN ROBERTS: Now I guess
