of quantum mechanics

00:34:10.560 --> 00:34:13.239
that it only predicts
probabilities.

00:34:13.239 --> 00:34:16.569
It does not predict exactly what
happens in a given experiment.

00:34:20.070 --> 00:34:27.239
However, we use--
Simon Kochen and I

00:34:27.239 --> 00:34:30.870
in proving our free
will theorem-- use

00:34:30.870 --> 00:34:32.840
a part of quantum mechanics.

00:34:32.840 --> 00:34:37.179
In some circumstances it
predicts a probability of one

00:34:37.179 --> 00:34:39.730
that something or other happens.

00:34:39.730 --> 00:34:43.545
That is really an absolute
prediction in a certain sense.

00:34:47.380 --> 00:34:50.949
